  <chapter xml:id="install-intro.install" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
    <title>Installation</title>
    <para>
      If you haven't installed HHVM, Hack and/or XHP yet, you will want to
      do that before continuing.
      <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
          <simpara><link xlink:href="&url.hhvm.getting-started;">
            Getting Started</link>
          </simpara>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <simpara>
            <link xlink:href="&url.hhvm.install.prebuilt;">
              Prebuilt-Packages
            </link>
          </simpara>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            <link linkend="install.hack">
              Install Hack
            </link>
            <itemizedlist>
              <listitem>
                <simpara>
                  <link xlink:href="&url.hack.tutorial;">
                    Hack Tutorial
                  </link>
                </simpara>
              </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <simpara>
            <link linkend="install.xhp">
              Install XHP
            </link>
          </simpara>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </para>
    <note>
      <para> HHVM on Windows is currently unsupported </para>
    </note>
    <note>
      <para>
        <link xlink:href="&url.hhvm.install.cloud.heroku;">
          Heroku
        </link>
        provides HHVM instances in its cloud infrastructure.
      </para>
    </note>
    <note>
      <para>
        Mac OS X does not currently have pre-built packages, but you can
        manually
        <link xlink:href="&url.hhvm.install.compile;">
          compile HHVM
        </link>
        for the Mac.
      </para>
    </note>
